                ],
                "institute": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " 250 KEV ACCELERATOR OF THE INSTITUT FUER RADIUM-",
                " FORSCHUNG UND KERNPHYSIK."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " 14.1 MEV NEUTRONS."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A REACTION CHAMBER WITH 32 TELESCOPES MOUNTED",
                " AT DIFFERENT ANGLES WERE USED. THE ENERGY SCALE WAS",
                " CALIBRATED WITH RECOIL PROTONS AT 24 DEGREES FROM A",
                " POLYETHYLENE FOIL, GIVING PROTONS OF ABOUT 12 MEV",
                " ENERGY. IN ADDITION, 5 MEV ALPHA-PARTICLES FROM AN",
                " AM-241 SOURCE WAS OBSERVED. IN TOTAL, THE ENERGY SCALE",
                " WAS ESTABLISHED TO BETTER THAN 200 KEV. THE ANGULAR",
                " RESOLUTION OF THE TELESCOPES WAS ON AVERAGE 13",
                " DEGREES."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": null,
                "reaction": {
                  "code": "27-CO-59(N,2N)27-CO-58,,SIG",
                  "code_unit": [
                    {
                      "unit": "27-CO-59(N,2N)27-CO-58,,SIG",
                      "field": {
                        "reaction": "27-CO-59(N,2N)27-CO-58",
                        "target": "27-CO-59",
                        "projectile": "N",
                        "process": "2N",
                        "product": "27-CO-58",
                        "quantity": ",SIG",
                        "data_type": null,
                        "general_quantity_modifier": null,
                        "quantity_236": ",SIG"
                      }
                    }
                  ],
                  "unit_combination": "(%)"
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                " THIS REACTION WAS USED AS",
                " ACTIVATION MONITOR. IN ADDITION, THE INTEGRAL NEUTRON",
                " FLUX WAS DETERMINED WITH A LITHIUM-IODIDE",
                " SCINTILLATION MONITOR. BOTH METHODS AGREED WITHIN 3",
                " PERCENT."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".THE SAMPLES WERE THICK COMPARED TO THE RANGE OF THE",
                " MOST ENERGETIC (14.7 MEV) PROTONS. METALLIC SILVER AND",
                " NIOBIUM SHEETS 0.7 MM THICK AND INDIUM SHEETS 1 MM",
                " THICK WERE USED. FOR BACKGROUND DETERMINATION A THICK",
                " GOLD TARGET REPLACED THE TARGET FOILS. THE SAMPLES",
                " WERE IRRADIATED FOR ABOUT 100 HOURS WITH A MAXIMUM",
                " NEUTRON FLUX OF 1.2000E+05 N/CM2SEC."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".THE BACKGROUND WAS SUBTRACTED."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " STANDARD DEVIATION. TOTAL ERRORS WERE A",
                " COMBINATION OF STATISTICAL AND IDENTIFIED SYSTEMATIC",
                " ERRORS, SUCH AS UNCERTAINTIES IN THE NEUTRON FLUX (3",
                " PERCENT) AND IN THE SOLID ANGLE OF THE CENTRAL",
                " DETECTOR (2 PERCENT), ERROR IN THE DE/DX VALUES (3",
                " PERCENT), AND ERRORS DUE TO THE DATA REDUCTION PROCE-",
                " DURE (2 PERCENT)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".UNFOLDING OF THE THICK TARGET SPECTRA."
              ]
            }
          ],
